📘 PHP Homework - 3

This repository contains solutions for Homework 3 focused on practicing core PHP programming concepts such as functions, arrays, and logical problem-solving.

🚀 Project Overview

The objective of this homework is to strengthen understanding of PHP by implementing multiple functions and testing them using a separate PHP file.

The project follows a structured approach:

Writing reusable PHP functions
Avoiding direct output inside functions
Returning results and testing separately
📂 Project Structure
homework-3/
│── homework3.php        # Main file containing all PHP functions
│── README.md            # Project documentation
🛠️ Features
📌 Implementation of multiple PHP functions
📌 Use of arrays and associative arrays
📌 Function-based logic building
📌 Separate testing file for validation
📌 Clean and modular coding approach
💻 Technologies Used
PHP
HTML (for testing output)
XAMPP / Local Server
⚙️ How to Run
Install XAMPP or any PHP server

Place the project folder inside:

htdocs/
Start Apache server

Open browser and run:

http://localhost/homework-3/hw3_testing.php
📖 Learning Outcomes
Understanding PHP syntax and functions
Working with arrays and data structures
Writing reusable and modular code
Testing PHP functions effectively
